Commentary.Commentary: We are set to begin! The New Zealand players take the field. Followed by Shadman Islam and Mahmudul Hasan Joy who walk out to bat for Bangladesh. Tim Southee to start with the ball.
... Second innings ...

Not what New Zealand envisioned for themselves. Their plan would’ve been to get 400 runs on the board but credit to Bangladesh spinners who spun a web around the batters and restricted the Kiwis to 328 runs. Mehidy Hasan led the bowling attack for the visitors and he picked up 3 wickets. Mominul Haque took the final wicket to end things for the Kiwis. Henry Nicholls could not get much support from the other end, he fought a lone battle and if not for him New Zealand would've never crossed the 300-run mark.

OUT! TAKEN! Mominul Haque gets the final wicket to end New Zealand's innings. Tossed up, on middle. Henry Nicholls goes for the reverse sweep but couldn't get past backward point. Shadman Islam this time shows good reflexes and grabs it. NEW ZEALAND HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 328!
Commentary.Howout: c Shadman Islam b Mominul Haque

UltraEdge shows there was a spike when the ball passed the bat. Excellent review from Bangladesh. So, Neil Wagner walks back for a golden duck. Mehidy Hasan is on a hat-trick now.
Commentary.Howout: c Liton Das b Mehidy Hasan

We are set for the first session! The players stride out to the middle. Henry Nicholls walks out in the middle and is accompanied by Rachin Ravindra. Ebadot Hossain to complete his over.

Bangladesh on the other hand, need wickets. Shoriful Islam was the pick of the lot and needs support from the other end to scalp the remaining 5 wickets and try to restrict New Zealand under 300. An interesting first session coming up shortly.

New Zealand would want to post a big first innings total. The foundation was laid by Devon Conway and Will Young and with Henry Nicholls still on the crease, the Kiwis would look to pile as many runs as possible. In posting a hundred on Saturday, Conway became just the sixth man in history and the first since Michael Clarke in 2004 to score a century in his first Tests at both home and away. Australian duo Harry Graham and Kepler Wessels, Pakistan's Azhar Mahmood and England's Sir Andrew Strauss are the other men to achieve the rare feat.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 2 of the first Test between New Zealand and Bangladesh. New Zealand will be fairly satisfied with the runs they have on the board while Bangladesh would be happy too as the bowlers chipped up 3 wickets in the final session of Day 1 and didn't let their opponents run away with the game. Let's see what Day 2 has in store for us.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Right then! The visitors will be happy with the wickets they picked in the final session and would look to build on the same. New Zealand, on the flip side, would want Henry Nicholls to bat for long and get close to the 350-run mark. The action continues on Sunday, January 2, 2022. The first ball will be bowled at 3.30 am IST (10 pm GMT, previous day). But the build-up will begin much in advance. Do join us for that. Till then, cheers!

Devon Conway is up for a chat. He says that it was very challenging to bat upfront and the wicket was green. Mentions that it got a lot better lately and is happy to contribute. Tells that Bangladesh bowled pretty well and it was all about being patient. Adds that they are disappointed that they lost Tom Blundell at the end but feels that they are still in a strong position. On his wicket, he says that it is the last way one wants to get out after all the hard work but that's how it goes.

Bangladesh started the first hour of the day really well but looked to have lost their track as the ball kept getting old and there was no movement off it. The pitch too got better and better to bat. Bangladesh bowlers toiled very hard and gained rewards with three wickets in the final session. That would certainly boost their confidence after ending the day on a positive note.

After losing Tom Latham early on and Will Young before Tea, Devon Conway and Ross Taylor batted really well and the runs kept coming at a brisk rate after the Tea break. Taylor was struggling to find the middle of the blade initially but got into his rhythm and struck some beautiful shots but unfortunately, he slipped out once he tried to up his ante. Later, Nicholls came in and made his intentions clear with his aggressive shots. But soon after, Conway was sent back as well and at the stroke of Stumps, they lost Tom Blundell as well. The Kiwis are still in a commonding position though and would look to pile as many runs as possible on Day 2.

What a great comeback by the visitors in the final session of the day. It was all about New Zealand in the first two sessions, but the hosts lost Devon Conway who was well set and then lost Tom Blundell at the stroke of Stumps. Bangladesh would be happy with their bowling performance and would hope to end things early on Day 2.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Bangladesh do get a wicket in the final over of the day. Back of a length, outside off, Tom Blundell stands up on his toes and looks to punch. Plays a little late as the ball goes off the inside edge and goes back to disturb the stumps. Bangladesh would have loved a couple of wickets in the final session and they have got exactly that. Tom Blundell walks back dejected. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Commentary.Howout: b Ebadot Hossain

Session 2 Summary - 81runs, 0 wickets, 27 overs. Clearly, this session belonged to the hosts. Yes, they did lose Will Young but before that, he and Devon Conway continued post Lunch to blunt the Bangladesh bowling attack. The duo kept motoring along and also brought up their individual fifties. The track eased out considerably and it looked like Bangladesh would have a wicketless session but credit to some good piece of fielding, they saw the back of Will Young. Devon Conway on his return has been looking in good touch and is inching closer to his century. Bangladesh would dearly love a wicket or two post Tea to get some momentum but will have to be more disciplined with the ball. While New Zealand look in a good position and would look to continue to do so especially with the pitch assisting the batters. Do join us at 8.30 am IST (3 pm GMT) for the final session.

Bangladesh seamers were on the money in the opening hour of the session and got an important wicket of Latham. Later, they were unable to cause much threat and leaked handful runs. The bowlers though kept their lines and lengths tight just to build some pressure on the hosts. Even though they were not rewarded, the visitors would look to continue on their good way. Will the Bangla bowlers be able to get a couple of wickets? Or will the hosts remain solid in their defense? To find out, do join us for the second session at 6.10 am IST (12.40 am GMT).

It was not a good start for the hosts, they lost their skipper, Tom Latham, pretty early on. Then a steady stand between Conway and Young made sure they remain unscathed till Lunch. Certainly after the drinks break, the runs came in a convincingly good rate for the Kiwis. The pair stitched a crucial partnership of 65 runs.

FOUR! Conway gets away with this one! Back of a length, outside off. Devon Conway looks to pull. The ball goes off the top edge and flies over the keeper's head for a boundary.
Fuller in length, on off. Devon Conway pushes it to mid off.
Length ball, on off. Tapped towards covers for a single.

On a length, on middle, coming back in. Devon Conway looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. The ball lobs up in the air and goes towards point. The fielder catches it and appeals for a catch but the umpire is unmoved.
On a good length, on off. Devon Conway looks to defend but the ball hits the handle of the bat.
On a length, on middle. Devon Conway is solid in his defence.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Full again, on middle. Devon Conway flicks it through mid-wicket for another boundary. 50-run partnership comes up between these two.
FOUR! Nicely played! Fuller in length, on off. Devon Conway drives it past the diving mid on fielder and collects a boundary. Glorious on-drive that!
Good-length ball, outside off. Will Young looks to punch but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, on middle. Will Young defends it watchfully.
On a length, outside off. Will Young leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, on middle. Devon Conway flicks it to deep mid-wicket. The fielder cuts it off and keeps it down to three runs.
On a length, on off. Devon Conway plays it on the leg side.
Length ball, on middle. Devon Conway clips it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Back of a length, around off. Will Young evades the line and leaves it untouched.
Devon Conway works this full ball to mid on for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Full and on off. Blocked out.

Short of a length, on middle. Will Young pulls it without any timing to deep backward square leg. He carries it on a bounce. The fielder was in two minds there, whether to charge ahead to collect it or not. In the end, doesn't as the ball was travelling very fast. Shoriful Islam is really disappointed there. He feels the fielder should have opted for a catch.
On a length, outside off. Will Young lets it sail through.
A single to end the over! On a length, on middle. Will Young clips it to mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length, on middle. Will Young looks to work it on the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pads.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Fuller, outside off. Pushed towards covers.
Short of a length, on middle. Will Young mistimes his pull back to the bowler.
Little bit loose from Will Young. He needs to be more disciplined. This was very full, outside off. Will Young looks to drive but fails to connect.
On middle, Devon Conway defends it out.
That's gone through gully! On a length, on middle, angling away. Will Young looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge past the diving gully fielder for a single.
On the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Length ball, angling away, outside off. Will Young shoulders arms.
On a good length, on middle. Will Young clips it to mid-wicket.
Good start from Shoriful Islam! Good-length ball, on off. Devon Conway looks to push. The ball goes off the inner half to square leg for a run.
On a length, on off. Will Young stays solid in his defence.
FOUR! Exquisite timing! Length ball, on middle. Will Young prods and drives it past mid on. The fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race. A boundary.
On a good length,outside off. Will Young is happy to leave that one alone. This is where New Zealand have been very good. Leaving balls that are outside off stump.
Fuller in length, on middle. Pushed back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle. Will Young looks to pull but the ball perhaps stays a touch low. It goes off the bottom edge to the slip cordon.
On a good length, on off. Will Young dabs it through backward point and gully for a couple of runs.
On a length, on off. Devon Conway knocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over. Ebadot Hossain goes short now, on off. Devon Conway hangs back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Runs have started to flow now for New Zealand.

Good comeback from the bowler! Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. Devon Conway is all squared up in his defence. The ball zips past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. Hal-hearted appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire.

FOUR! Lovely shot and lovey piece of timing on that one! Length ball, outside off. Devon Conway plants his front foot and pushes it late. Hits it through covers and gets a boundary. No need to run for those.
Good-length ball, outside off. Devon Conway shoulders arms.
Fuller, outside off. Devon Conway does not offer any stroke to that one.
Fuller in length, on off. Will Young prods and drives it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, on middle now. Will Young looks to tuck but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length, on off. Will Young hops and defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on off. Will Young wrists it to deep square leg for a brace.
Switches to 'round the wicket. Fuller in length, outside off. Devon Conway nicely pushes it towards covers and rotates the strike.
On a good length, on middle. Devon Conway defends it down onto the deck.
Not far away from hitting the pads! Good-length ball, on middle, nipping in. Devon Conway nudges it to square leg. Taskin Ahmed will have to reload again as he has overstepped. No ball signalled.

DRINKS! A really good first hour of play for Bangladesh. They have got the Kiwi skipper, Tom Latham and are keeping things very tight. The seamers are doing their job well and would look to continue to do that. Meanwhile, Devon Conway and Will Young will look to keep the scoreboard ticking and remain unscathed till Lunch.
Full, on leg. Conway flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Conway stays back and looks to cut it away but misses, as the ball bounces over his blade.
Fuller and on off. Conway defends it out solidly.
Short and outside off. Conway pulls it off the bottom end towards mid on. The fielder there dives to his right to make the stop.
Length and outside off. Conway leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full and outside off. Conway defends it out to the off side.
Back of a length, outside off. Young shuffles across and shoulders his arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off. Young defends it to cover.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
Back of a length, outside off. Young punches it to point off the back foot.
Full and outside off. Young blocks it to mid off.
Taskin Ahmed (4-3-1-0) is back into the attack.
On a length, on off. Devon Conway plays it towards covers.
Good timing on that one but will only get two! Fuller, outside off. Devon Conway drives it through covers for a couple.
Good running! On the pads, fuller. Will Young flicks it to deep square leg. He calls for two and gets it. Devon Conway races back for the third run and gets it comfortably.
Good-length ball, on middle, angling in. Will Young defends it out.
Back of a length, on middle. Will Young stands up on his toes and blocks it out.
Fuller, on middle. Devon Conway works it to mid-wicket for a run.
Short ball and on off. Young ducks under it and leaves it alone.
Short and on middle. Conway pulls it through square leg for a single.
Full length and on off. Conway defends it to point solidly.
Good-length ball, outside off, Conway lets it go to the keeper.
Length and on leg. Young tucks it to square leg for a run.
FOUR! Young gets off the mark with a boundary. First boundary of the innings as well. Fuller, on middle and leg. Young comes forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full length and on off. Conway strides forward and defends it to mid off.
Short ball and outside off. Conway leaves it alone watchfully for the keeper.
Good length, outside off. Conway keeps his blade close to his body and lets the ball sail past him.
Back of a length and outside off. Conway shoulders his arms to it.
Full and on off. Conway presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Length and wide outside off. Conway leaves it alone watchfully.
Ebadot Hossain comes into the attack. He replaces Taskin Ahmed.
Full length and on off. Young defends it back to the bowler.
Nicely bowled! On a length, outside off, shaping away from the right-hander. Young gets on his front foot and looks to defend it out but misses.
Conway is off the mark now. Good length, on off. Conway defends it to cover and gets across to the other end.

CLOSE! Both the batters are yet to get off the mark. On a length, outside off, shaping in. Conway shoulders his arms and leaves it alone. The ball comes back in nicely and goes over the stumps. Good leave by Conway though.
On a length, wide outside off. Conway leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full, around middle and leg. Conway flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Good length and outside off. Young shoulders his arms to it.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on leg. Young looks to defend it but misses. He gets rapped on the pads. Ahmed appeals but the umpire is unmoved. Probably sliding down leg.
Fuller and sliding down leg. Young looks to flick it away but misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Young does not chase it at all.
Length and on off. Young defends it out solidly.

Full length and outside off. Conway looks to drive it away. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of gully. The fielder there dives to his right to make a good stop. This one just fell short of the man there. Third consecutive maiden for Shoriful Islam.
Good length and wide outside off, Conway shoulders his arms.
Length ball, on off. Devon Conway nudges it to mid on.
Touch fuller, outside off. Conway watches the ball closely and makes a leave.
Full length and on off. Conway blocks it out.

Bangladesh have taken a review for an LBW. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved. Ball Tracking shows that the ball is pitching outside off, the impact is umpire's call and it is umpire's call on wickets hitting as well. The original decision stays. Bangladesh retain their review.

NOT OUT! Devon Conway survives. This was really, really close but the umpire's call helps Conway to stay in the middle. A length ball, outside off, shaping in. Conway looks to defend it out but misses and gets hit on the pads. Shoriful Islam appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Shoriful Islam convinces his skipper and they take the review. It shows umpire's call on impact and ball hitting the wicket. Bangladesh do not lose a review here.
Touch short and outside off. Young leaves it alone without any hesitation.
Good length, outside off. The ball flies off the deck. Young leaves it alone. Das collects it besides his head.
Short and outside off, Young shoulders his arms.
Length and outside off, Young blocks it to point.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Young leaves it alone for the keeper.
BEATEN! Good bounce and carry. On a length, outside off, shaping away a bit. Young looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller and on the stumps. Conway was thinking about leaving it but in the end he defended out watchfully. A wicket-maiden from Shoriful Islam!
Back of a length, outside off, left alone.
Fuller and outside off. Conway works it to mid-wicket off the inner half.
Devon Conway walks out to bat at No.3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Liton Das takes a stunner behind the stumps to sent back the Kiwi skipper, Tom Latham. A full-length ball, around off, Latham looks to drive it to the off side but gets an inside edge on it. The ball flies to the left of the keeper. Das dives low to his left to take a sharp catch. It wouldn't have carried to the first slip fielder and Liton Das has done really well to dive full stretch to his left and grab it one-handed. Tom Latham walks back to the pavilion for a timid score. He is livid with himself. Shoriful Islam is pumped up and has provided Bangladesh with an early breakthrough. Just what they needed.
Commentary.Howout: c Liton Das b Shoriful Islam

Commentary.Commentary: Good length and outside off, no movement this time. Latham covers his stumps and shoulders his arms to it.
Full and on off. Latham works it to mid on off the inner half.
Full length and on off. Young defends it out off the front foot.
Fuller and on leg. Young squeezes it out to mid on.
Ahmed firs in a yorker, in the blockhole. Young blocks it out solidly.
On a length, outside off, moving away. Young has no interest to play away from his body.
Fraction full and outside off, moving away. Young shoulders his arms.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Young leave it alone for the keeper.
Length and on off. Latham defends it out. A maiden to start with for Islam.
Full and on leg. Latham flicks it to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone by Latham.
Touch fuller, outside off. It flies off the deck and nips in a bit. Latham shoulders his arms and the ball brushes off his thigh pads towards the keeper.
Length and outside off. Latham leaves it alone yet again.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Latham leaves it alone for the keeper.
Shoriful Islam to bowl from the other end.

Switches back to over the wicket to the right-hander. Good-length ball, around off, nipping away. Will Young looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. Good first over from Taskin Ahmed. He is getting the ball to move nicely. Just a single off it.
Tom Latham is underway! A shapr inswinger, on off. Tom Latham pushes at it. The ball goes off the inside half of the bat to mid-wicket for a run.

Lovely stuff! Taskin Ahmed switches to 'round the wicket and bowls a good-length ball, on middle, jagging back a long way. Tom Latham doesn't read the line and he shoulders arms. He gets hit near the box. Half an appeal for an LBW but it was going well over the stumps.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Tom Latham shoulders arms.
Little fuller this time, on off. Tom Latham covers the line and pushes it to mid off again.
Hint of swing straightaway! Length delivery, on off, coming back in, at 133 clicks. Latham pushes it to mid off.

Done with the pre-match formalities. We are set to begin now! The players of Bangladesh stride out to the middle. The players take their respective fielding positions. Tom Latham and Will Young are the openers for New Zealand. Taskin Ahmed to start the proceedings with the ball. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...
Both teams stride out to the middle and line up for the National Anthem. It will be Bangladesh's first followed by New Zealand's.

Bangladesh (Playing XI) - Shadman Islam, Mahmudul Hasan Joy, Najmul Hossain Shanto, Mominul Haque (C), Mushfiqur Rahim, Liton Das (WK), Yasir Ali, Mehidy Hasan, Taskin Ahmed, Ebadot Hossain, Shoriful Islam.
New Zealand (Playing XI) - Tom Latham (C), Will Young, Devon Conway, Ross Taylor, Henry Nicholls, Tom Blundell (WK), Rachin Ravindra, Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Neil Wagner, Trent Boult.
TOSS - Up goes the coin and it lands in the favor of Bangladesh. They have elected to BOWL first.

Bangladesh come into the series as underdogs but will be eager to punch above their weights despite their poor record. Mominul Haque has a massive responsibility on his shoulders and has lot to prove in this series. He will already be without their main gun, Shakib Al Hasan and will also miss the services of Tamim Iqbal. While Mahmudullah has retired from the format and thus, a lot relies on the skipper and the veteran Mushfiqur Rahim. Given all that, it is going to take a herculean effort from the visitors to register their first WTC points. Will they be able to do so? We will find out over the course of the next 5 days. Toss and team news in a bit. And, wishing you all a Happy New Year once again!

New Zealand will be without Kane Williamson and also have surprisingly left out Ajaz Patel who claimed all 10 wickets against India in the first innings of the second Test. But Tom Latham will be with his entire frontline pace attack. Devon Conway is also set to return after an injury. This series will be special for another reason, as veteran batter Ross Taylor announced retirement from international cricket and this two Tests will be his final hurrah in the longest format.

On the flip side, Bangladesh have had a disastrous 2021 atleast in the longest format of the game. They have lost five Tests, drew one and their solitary win came against Zimbabwe. To add salt to the injury, their record in New Zealand is something they wouldn't want to look at. Can they turn things this time around?

New Zealand are coming into this series after a 1-0 loss against India. The same side against whom they won the inaugural World Test Championship. Now their next challenge is Bangladesh. Tom Latham is set to don the captaincy hat as Kane Williamson is ruled out of the series with a shoulder injury. The Kiwis' home record against Bangladesh is superb as they have played 9 Tests and have won all of them. Can they continue their home dominance against the Bangla Tigers?

First of all, Happy New Year to everyone! First day of the new year and it kick starts with the longest format of the game. The World Test Championship winners will start their home summer against Bangladesh in a two-match Test series. The first Test will take place at Bay Oval, Mount Maunganui. On that note, welcome to the coverage.
... MATCH DAY ...

We are back for the third innings! A tricky little phase for the Kiwi opening batters. The players of Bangladesh stride out to the middle, followed by Tom Latham and Will Young who walk out to bat for New Zealand. Taskin Ahmed to start with the ball.
...Third innings...

Well, New Zealand had to toil hard in the middle to get those 10 wickets and they must be drained out. All of their pace bowlers bowled more than 30 overs and they had to work hard for their wickets as the tourists showed great fight. In the end, Trent Boult finished with 4 wickets to his name, while Neil Wagner picked up 3. However, it was Tim Southee who looked the most promising bowler in the first session on Day 4 and he picked up a couple. The Kiwis now have their task cut out as they trail by 130 runs and their batters need to start well. Will Tom Latham lead from the front in the second innings? We'll find that soon. Do join us for the third innings which begins shortly.

Bangladesh have batted really well and most importantly, it hasn't been a one-man show. All of their batters have chipped in and that has resulted in them posting a huge total on the board. The only thing that didn't go their way is that none of their batters managed to get a hundred. However, Mominul Haque will be more than pleased with the way they have replied to New Zealand's first innings score.

End of a brilliant innings for Bangladesh and they would be extremely pleased with their effort. They have batted their skins out against the Kiwis and they would have certainly taken this score at the start of the Test. They are in the driver's seat now and the hosts are in a spot of bother.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Trent Boult wraps things up finally for New Zealand! Boult keeps it simple, serves a full ball, onto the stumps. Shoriful Islam backs away, exposes his stumps, goes for the drive but gets beaten altogether. The ball beats the edge and knocks the off stump over. BANGLADESH END ON 458 and THEY LEAD BY 130 RUNS.
Commentary.Howout: b Trent Boult

Commentary.Commentary: Short ball, outside off. Shoriful Islam makes room and throw his arms at it, but fails to get any bat on it.
Ebadot Hossain is the last man in.

OUT! LBW! Tim Southee strikes again and sends Taskin Ahmed back to the hut. A length ball, angling it in onto the pads. Taskin Ahmed misses his flick and gets rapped on the pads. A huge shout for LBW and the umpire raises his finger. Taskin Ahmed reviews it straightaway. The replays roll in. UltraEdge confirms that there is no bat involved. Ball Tracker indicates that it would have clipped the leg stump. It is umpire's call and Bangladesh do not lose a review here, but lose a wicket.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Tim Southee

Commentary.Commentary: Taskin Ahmed reviews it straightaway! He has been adjudged LBW but this one looks like it would have clipped the leg stump. No bat involved confirms the UltraEdge and the Ball tracker indicates that it would have clipped the leg stump. It is umpire's call and Bangladesh do not lose a review.
Length, outside off. Taskin Ahmed blocks it out.
Another full delivery, outside off. Shoriful Islam drives it towards deep cover. A single taken.

Shoriful Islam takes the aerial route this time! Tim Southee serves a full ball, outside off. Shoriful Islam makes room and lofts over covers. The ball won't go all the way but the batters take two comfortable runs.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Shoriful Islam drives it to cover.
A length ball, angling in on middle. Taskin Ahmed looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
Short ball, down leg. Shoriful Islam ducks udnerneath watchfully.
FOUR! Crucial runs these for Bangladesh! Full ball, outside off. Shoriful Islam throws his bat at it and the ball goes past the mid off fielder for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Shoriful Islam blocks it out.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Shoriful Islam looks to dig it out but he misses.
Length ball, angling down leg. Shoriful Islam misses his flick.
Shoriful Islam walks out to the middle now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Oh, what an unfortunate way to get out and Yasir Ali would be absolutely gutted to get out in that manner! Jamieson serves a length ball, angling in down leg. Ali looks to flick but he gets a tickle on it. Tom Blundell, behind the sticks, does well to move across to his left and pouch it. Bangladesh lose another wicket and Jamieson is delighted!
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: Full ball, drifting onto the pads. Taskin Ahmed flicks it uppishly but the ball falls just short of the mid-wicket fielder.
Banged into the deck, around middle. Taskin Ahmed ducks underneath.
Back of a length, outside off. Taskin Ahmed stays back, opens the face of his bat and taps it towards the gully fielder.
Good-length ball, around off. Taskin Ahmed blocks it out.
FOUR! A shot of some real authority from Ahmed! On a length, outside off. Ahmed stands tall, gets on top of the bounce and flat-bats it straight back past the bowler to fetch himself a boundary.
Full ball, angling in from middle. Taskin Ahmed clips it behind square on the leg side. The fielder at short fine leg does well to stop it by diving low to his right.
Back of a length, outside off. Yasir Ali gets behind the line of the ball to block this one out.
On a length, outside off. Yasir Ali drives but finds the mid off fielder.
Wide! A bumper, well above Ali's head. Ali lets it go through to the keeper and the umpire stretches his arms to signal a wide.
Good-length ball, around off. Yasir Ali punches it to cover.
A wayward ball, down leg. Yasir Ali misses his flick.
On a length, around off. Yasir Ali defends it off the front foot.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Yasir Ali tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, around middle. Taskin Ahmed blocks it out back to the bowler.
A well-directed bumper from Southee, around middle. Taskin Ahmed ducks underneath.
Full ball, angling down leg. Taskin Ahmed misses his flick.
Taskin Ahmed comes to the crease now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Tim Southee strikes and New Zealand get the much-needed breakthrough! A sigh of relief from Southee and Hasan's fighting knock comes to an end. This was a slightly shorter ball, outside off and shaping away late. Mehidy Hasan stays back and looks to cut but he only manages an outside edge towards the keeper. Tom Blundell behind the sticks makes no mistake and Bangladesh lose their seventh wicket now. Hasan walks back disappointed as he misses out on a well-deserved fifty.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Tim Southee

Commentary.Commentary: Length ball, around off. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out.
FOUR! EDGY! Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan sees the width and throws the kitchen sink at it. It goes off the thick outside edge and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Length ball, angling in from middle. Yasir Ali prods and gets solid in his defense.
Another full ball, around middle. Yasir Ali looks to block but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards square leg.
Jamieson goes a bit fuller this time, around middle. Yasir Ali defends it out.
On a length, outside off and shaping away late. Yasir Ali leaves it alone.
Lovely delivery! Good length ball, outside off and shaping away late. Yasir Ali looks to poke at it but the ball beats his outside edge.
Length ball, jagging back in sharply, from off. Yasir Ali turns it to mid-wicket.

DRINKS! Well, Bangladesh continue their dominance in this Test as they have managed to survive the first hour on Day 4 without losing any wicket. They now lead by 113 runs and New Zealand badly need wickets with this new ball as runs are coming quite easily for the tourists.
Shortish delivery, around off. Mehidy Hasan dabs it towards gully.
Shortish ball, on the thigh pads again. Yasir Ali taps it past square leg for a single.
Trent Boult goes over the wicket now, serves a length ball, outside off. Yasir Ali pushes it to cover.
Touch shorter, on the thigh pads. Mehidy Hasan tucks it away towards fine leg. A single taken.
Another length ball, on the pads this time. Mehidy Hasan defends this one to mid-wicket.
Length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan pushes it back to the bowler.
Swinging it in this time, on middle. Yasir Ali blocks it out.

NEARLY CHOPPED ON! Back of a length, outside off. Yasir Ali, on the back foot, looks to cut this away, but manages to get a bottom edge. The ball bounces on the turf and goes just over the stumps. Yasir Ali gets lucky here.
Good length, outside off. Yasir Ali shoulders arms to it.
Another length ball, wide of off. Yasir Ali lets that go through.
Length ball, shaping away from outside off. Left alone.

Good-length delivery, on the pads. Yasir Ali, on the back foot, tucks it to fine leg. The batters take two runs, but hang on, the umpire signals for a short run, as Ali is short of his crease as he turned for the second. One run given.
Length ball, outside off. Yasir Ali pushes it to cover.
LEG BYE! A fuller delivery, on the pads. Mehidy Hasan misses his flick and gets rapped on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters steal a leg bye.
FOUR! Top shot! A shortish delivery, outside off. Mehidy Hasan hangs back and pushes it through covers for a boundary.
Wide! Too short on this occasion. Mehidy Hasan just ducks under it. Wide called as the ball went way over Hasan's head.
Good length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan plays that to point.
On a length, on middle. This time Mehidy Hasan hangs back and blocks it out.
Full in length, on middle. Mehidy Hasan, on front foot, drives it to the man at cover.
Full, outside off. Yasir Ali offers no shot on that. Dot to end the over and a maiden over to start with!
Fuller, down the leg side this time. Yasir Ali lets that go through.
Back of a length, outside off. Yasir Ali leaves it alone.
Shortish delivery, outside off. Yasir Ali, on the back foot, pushes it wide of the short cover fielder, who dives and makes a good stop there.
Touch fuller, on the pads. Yasir Ali flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Kyle Jamieson begins with a low full toss ball, around off. Yasir Ali pushes it back to the bowler.
Kyle Jamieson (30-9-72-0) comes into the attack. He replaces Tim Southee.
Touch shorter, outside off. Hasan pushes it to cover point.
Nipping back in onto the pads, and on a length, Mehidy Hasan blocks it out on the leg side.
FOUR! Cleverly done! A length ball, onto the pads. Mehidy Hasan, on the back foot, just tickles it away towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. The lead is now past 100!
Back of a length, on the body. Yasir Ali pulls it gently towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Change of angle now, Trent Boult goes 'round the wicket, serves a shortish delivery, outside off. Yasir Ali blocks it towards point.
Good-length delivery, shaping it onto the pads. Yasir Ali flicks it past square leg for a brace.
Back of a length, around off. Mehidy Hasan defends it off the back foot.
Southee bangs it into the deck, around middle. Mehidy Hasan ducks underneath.
Another ball, on a length, just outside off and curling away late. Mehidy Hasan prods but decides to leave it in the end.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, around off and shaping away late. Mehidy Hasan lets it be.
Short of a length, outside off. Yasir Ali stays back and cuts it over the point fielder. The batters take a single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Yasir Ali leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan does not offer any shot to this one.

Oh, dear! How did that miss the off stump? This is a peach of a delivery from Boult and Hasan is very lucky to get away with it! Length ball, just outside off and angling in late. Mehidy Hasan leaves it and the ball goes just past the off pole.
Short of a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan defends it out.
On a length, around off. Mehidy Hasan hangs back and blocks it to the off side.

FOUR! Nicely controlled by Hasan! Boult bangs it into the deck, around leg. Hasan stays back and pulls it along the ground behind square on the leg side for a bounday. This will surely frustrate Boult.

We are set for Day 4 to get underway! The players of New Zealand stride out to the middle and they are followed by Bangladesh's overnight batters, Yasir Ali and Mehidy Hasan. Rachin Ravindra will start with the ball.

New Zealand bowlers bowled their hearts out on Day 3 but it was only Trent Boult and Neil Wagner who managed to get into the wickets column. Surprisingly, the Kiwis have bowled 156 overs so far and yet they haven't been able to take those 10 wickets, especially in home conditions. This sums up the entire story and also tells us how well the tourists have batted against the pace attack of New Zealand. The Kiwi bowlers would be a bit weary coming into Day 4 but they will need to make sure that they get the remaining wickets without conceding too many runs if they are to have any chance of winning this Test. Lots of things to look forward to on Day 4 which promises to be a cracker. Stay tuned for further updates.

Bangladesh have made their intentions very clear in the first Test by putting on a show with the bat and they are firmly in the driver's seat now. Their top order has done a terrific job of batting out time as well as piling up runs as the number of runs scored in the first innings decide the outcome of the match more often than not. The tourists now have a decent lead but the overnight batters will be eager to bat long and score as many runs as possible so that they get a substantial lead which will also ensure that New Zealand do not get a chance to come back into the contest.

Hello and a very warm welcome to the coverage of Day 4 of the first Test between New Zealand and Bangladesh. So far, we have witnessed enthralling 3 days of Test cricket and we go into Day 4 with the tourists having the edge over the Kiwis. Yes, you read that right. It is Bangladesh who lead by 73 runs in the first innings and the hosts need to make sure that Bangladesh do not run away with the lead on Day 4.

A late joy for the hosts, as they saw the backs of the two set batters in the final session, thanks to Trent Boult. The bowlers were made to toil really hard today and these couple of wickets would make them happy but not enough as the visitors kept piling on the pressure with every run, they put on the scoreboard. The Kiwis would look to pick up the remaining wickets quickly and come out to bat as soon as possible.

This has been the longest ever Test innings played by Bangladesh overseas. This tells you everything about their batting performance today. Even though they lost two scalps in the morning session. Haque and Das made sure they get the repair work done and get their noses in front. The pair batted throughout the second session and would’ve loved to repeat the same in the final session but that was not the case. Both the batsmen were sent back in their 80s and would be absolutey gutted. Later though, Mehidy Hasan and Yasir Ali scored at a brisk rate and ended their day without losing any more wickets.

New Zealand tried everything out of the box, but Bangladesh batters had all the answers and negotiated really well with the blade. But in the final hour of the final session, Boult put his hand up and struck in quick succession to get rid of both the set batters, Mominul Haque and Liton Das. But Bangladesh have done really well to keep the runs ticking and extend their lead to 73 runs.

The hosts have been completely outplayed here, they failed to grab any wickets in this session and are in desperate need of a wicket. Mominul Haque and Liton Das have looked calm and composed. While Das has been scoring runs at a quick rate, Mominul Haque has been patient in the middle and is leading from the front. After a noteworthy batting performance on Day 2, Bangladesh have been all over the place here. They could not find their rhythm out there in the middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy played an impressive knock, but he was unable to hold on to his innings and make it big. Mominul Haque is struggling but is still out there in the middle. Bangladesh trail by 108 runs and one big partnership is all that they need to get things under control.

An exceptional bowling performance from New Zealand. They did not allow the batters to score freely, kept adding pressure, and most importantly grabbed two important scalps. Neil Wagner was the man to dismiss Mahmudul Hasan Joy, soon Trent Boult followed that with a peach of a delivery to dismiss Mushfiqur Rahim. Although, Kyle Jamieson might have not picked up a wicket, but he was right on the money. He certainly put up an impactful performance with the ball. New Zealand will come into the next session with some confidence and will be hoping to grab a few more wickets.

That was an exciting session of Test cricket. New Zealand have come back stronger and picked up 2 scalps in the session. They will be mighty pleased with their performance this morning. The visitors on the other hand, will not be satisfied with their show. They only have managed to add 45 runs in this session, and have lost their experienced player, Mushfiqur Rahim and Mahmudul Hasan Joy who was looking in fine touch.

The World Test Champions had an off day, they lost quick wickets and were restricted to a score below 350, their bowlers too were not at their best. They would be hoping to pick up some early wickets in the day and put the pressure back on Bangladesh. The visitors have been exceptional so far, Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Shanto have given them the desired start. Mahmudul Hasan Joy is still out there and will be looking to carry the same kind of form. A lot of cricket still left in this game.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 3 of this intriguing Test between New Zealand and Bangladesh. It's been a tough battle between the two sides so far, but Day 2 completely belonged to the visitors. They would be looking to continue the same way. While New Zealand will be looking for some quick wickets and take things under control.

Right then. Bangladesh have their noses in front and would hope to continue on their merry way. While, the Kiwis will be looking forward for the second new ball to trouble the batters. The action continues on Monday at 3.30 am IST (10.00 pm GMT, previous day). Till then take care and goodbye.

Not the day New Zealand would like! Traditionally, in New Zealand, teams always struggle to bat first and the team batting second gets the best of the pitches to bat on. However, given the home side's dominance in the last few years, it has managed to post totals in excess of 400 consistently while batting first and dismiss oppositions under 200 if bowling first. 2022 has not quite gone to that plan yet.Their bowlers toiled really hard in the sun but the batters were always up for the task and negotiated really well. But it was Wagner yet again who came to the rescue and broke a crucial partnership in the middle. The hosts would’ve thought they had a sniff but were not able to capitalize on it. Neil Wagner was the star of the pack for the Kiwis. The hosts would hope the moving day swings in their favour.

Bangladesh would've loved to see Shanto and Joy to see off the day but the former was sent back. Although, Joy and Haque made sure they do not loose any more wickets till Stumps. The runs came in at a brisk rate for the visitors and had some luck riding along with them. They now trail by 153 runs and the wicket is a friendly pitch to bat on as well. The batters would be eager to come out in the morning on Day 3.

End of a really good day for Bangladesh. It was their bowlers who set the tone and their batters continued the momentum. New Zealand were not able to cause much problems for the batters and Bangladesh batters cruised on this wicket.

Session Summary - 28 overs, 65 runs, 1 wicket. What an entertaining session! A good mix of attack and defence and ultimately, the session goes in favor of Bangladesh. Shadman Islam and Mahmudul Hasan Joy were motoring along really well and started to build a good partnership. But just when the partnership was blossoming, Neil Wagner scalped the wicket of Shadman Islam to provide New Zealand the breakthrough they were looking for. He bowled probing lines and lengths but was the only one to trouble the batters as he lacked support from the other end and that allowed Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Najmul Hossain Shanto to settle and bat the session out. There is still enough from the pitch to assist both, batters and bowlers. Should be a lively final session. Do join us at 8.30 am IST (3 am GMT) for that.

Back of a length, outside off, Joy leaves it alone for the keeper.
Kyle Jamieson comes 'round the wicket now and serves a full-length delivery, outside off. Shanto drives it through cover-point. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out.
Length ball, outside off, left alone by Shanto.
Length ball, on off. Shanto blocks it out solidly.
Full and wide outside off. Shanto looks to chase it but misses.
Length, on off, blocked out watchfully.
FOUR! Nicely played. Overpitched, full and on off. Shanto leans forward and pushes it through mid off for a boundary.
Full, on leg. Shanto flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Good length, outside off, shaping away a bit. Shanto looks to drive it through covers but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller and outside off. Shanto pushes it to the off side.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Joy rides the bounce and tucks it to square leg to rotate the strike.
A sharp bouncer on off. Joy ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Joy stays back and blocks it out.
Fuller and wide outside off. Shanto prods and pushes it towards cover.
Fuller, around middle and leg. Shanto clips it to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Full length, wide outside off. Shanto tries to squeeze it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, outside off. Shanto shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, on off. Shanto defends it back to the bowler.
Good length, outside off. Shanto chips it towards mid off.
Fuller and wide outside off. Joy leans in and drives it towards cover but not in the gap though.
Short yet again, on off. Joy blocks it out watchfully.
Back of a length, on off. Joy hangs back and blocks it out solidly.
Back of a length, outside off. Joy leaves it alone.
Length, on the stumps. Joy stays back and defends it out solidly.
Good length, outside off. Joy shoulders his arms.
Play and a miss! This is a loose shot from Shanto. On a length, wide outside off, enticing the batter to play at it. Shanto looks to push it away from his body but misses.
Fuller, on the pads. Joy tucks it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Full length ball, outside off. Joy works it through backward point for a brace.
Back of a length, outside off. Joy sits under this one.
FOUR! Timed that beautifully. Sliding in, towards middle and leg stump. Joy flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Length ball, around middle and leg. Joy plays it to mid-wicket off the inner half.

Short of a length, on middle. That shoots up after pitching. Najmul Hossain Shanto is all squared up in his defence and is taken aback by the bounce. Negotiated it well in the end as he left it alone.
Back of a length, on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto hops and blocks it out.
Full again, on the pads. Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it to deep square leg for a single 50 up for Bangladesh!
Fuller, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone.
Some late swing there! Length ball, outside off, swinging away. Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes it through covers for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it through covers for a brace.
Length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it out.
Outside off, on a length. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it be.
Fuller in length, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto looks to tuck but misses. He gets hit near the body. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters take a leg bye.
Short of a length, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it to the off side.

Kyle Jamieson is back into the attack.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it towards covers.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks under it.
On off, blocked out.

That looked pretty close! An inswinger, on middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to flick but misses. He gets hit on the pads. Loud appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no. Neil Wagner says he heard a noise there, indicating there was an inside edge. The Kiwis don't opt for the review here but the replay shows there wasn't an inside edge there and it would have been out.
Length ball, on off, nipping away a tad. Mahmudul Hasan Joy does well to defend it towards point.
Length ball, on off. Shanto defends it out.

Good length, wide outside off. Shanto leaves it alone.
On off, blocked out solidly.

Outside off, left alone.

Najmul Hossain Shanto walks out to bat at No.3.

Islam looks to flick it away but closes the face of the bat a little too early. The ball goes off the leading edge back towards the bowler. Wagner dives in front of him to complete the catch.
Commentary.Howout: c & b Neil Wagner

Commentary.Commentary: DRINKS! A great start for Bangladesh with the bat. Shadman Islam and Mahmudul Hasan Joy have been very solid so far. New Zealand bowlers asked a lot of questions but were unable to find the breakthrough. Bangladesh's opening pair will look to continue the positive work and would hope to remain unscathed till Tea.
Fuller in length, outside off. Well negotiated by Mahmudul Hasan Joy. Blocks it out watchfully.
Fuller, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy with a solid defence.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to the off side.

An inswinger from Tim Southee, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, tucked to fine leg for one.

Neil Wagner comes into the attack now.
Neil Wagner is brought into the attack now. He replaces Kyle Jamieson.
Beautifully bowled! On a good length, outside off, nipping away. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to defend. The ball whistles past the outside edge.
Length ball, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it out.

That swung back in sharply! Good-length ball, shaping in from off, on leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to defend but gets struck on the thigh pad. Half an appeal for an lbw but that was going down leg.
Outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy taps it to the off side.
Good-length ball, coming back in, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it out watchfully.
Full and wide outside off. Islam drives it to cover but straight to the fielder.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length, angled across the left-hander. Islam leaves it alone.
Length, down leg. Islam looks to flick it away but misses.
Length and on off. Islam blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off, shpaing away, Islam leaves it alone.
An inswinger, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it to mid on.
Fuller, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it to mid off.
On a length, on off. Mominul Haque blocks it out.
On off, Shadman Islam pushes it towards covers for a single.
Fuller in length, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets an inside edge as he tries to flick. The ball goes to mid-wicket for a single.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Goes full and wide, outside off. Shadman Islam lets it be.
Short of a length, on middle. Shadman Islam pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Shadman Islam shoulders arms.
On a length, on middle. Shadman Islam blocks it out.
On off, angling away. Shadman Islam defends it out.
On a good length, on off. Shadman Islam defends it out.
On a good length, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to the off side. Tody stuff from Tim Southee. Looks like change of ends has worked for him. Bowled on a lot better line and lengths.
Good-length ball, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it out off the front foot.
On a good length, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy covers the line and blocks it out.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy meets it with a dead bat.
Same line and length from Tim Southee, Shadman Islam looks to tuck it on the leg side. The ball goes off the pads and the batters take a leg bye.
Back of a length from 'round the wicket, on off. Shadman Islam looks to work it on the leg side but misses. Gets hit near the box.
Change of ends for Tim Southee!
On the pads, Shadman Islam tickles it one-handed to fine leg for a run.
Good-length ball, outside off, angling away. Shadman Islam with an easy leave.
Angling across the left-hander, outside off. Shadman Islam pushes it towards covers.
Back of a length again, on middle. Shadman Islam does well to block it out.
Back of a length, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it on the leg side for a single.
Starts with a good-length ball, outside off, moving away. Shadman Islam taps it through backward point for a single.
Kyle Jamieson comes into the attack. He replaces Tim Southee.
Fuller, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to drive. The ball goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, coming back in, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy clips it to short leg.
Back of a length, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tucks it on the leg side.
Short of a length, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it from the crease.
Short ball, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks under it.
Nearly chopped it on! Length ball, outside off. Shadman Islam looks to drive. The ball goes off the inside edge past the sumps to fine leg for a single.

Sprays another delivery down the leg side. Mahmudul Hasan Joy misses his flick. Southee clearly struggling for rhythm in this spell. Might not be a bad idea to give him a break. New Zealand will need to optimise the new ball.
Nicely pulled! Short of a length, on middle. Shadman Islam pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Shadman Islam punches it towards covers.
Good-length ball from 'round the wicket, outside off. Shadman Islam shoulders arms.
On the pads, this is flicked to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Good length but down the leg side, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it untouched.
Fullish, on off. Shadman Islam is very solid in his defence.
Back of a length, on off. Shadman Islam defends it solidly.
On a good length, on off. Shadman Islam blocks it out.
Good-length ball, outside off. Shadman Islam lets it sail through.
On a length, on off. Shadman Islam blocks it out.
On a good length, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tickles it to fine leg for a single.
On a good length, outside off. Shadman Islam pushes it through covers for a couple of runs.
On a good length, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tucks it on the leg side for a single.
Down the leg side, Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to flick but misses.
Outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it for the keeper to collect.
On a good length, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it out.
Beaten! Good-length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks for the expansive drive but the ball zips past the outside edge.

FOUR! Good aggressive shot that! Short of a length, on middle. Shadman Islam pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.

On a good length, on middle, nipping in. Mahmudul Hasan Joy nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.

Short of a length, outside off. Shadman Islam slashes it through extra cover for three runs.
Down the leg side, Mahmudul Hasan Joy misses his flick.

Goes wide of the crease and bowls a length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.

Good timing and good running! Length ball, on middle. Shadman Islam flicks it through mid-wicket for three runs.
That one shaped nicely! Good-length ball, nipping away, on leg. Shadman Islam looks to flick but misses.
Tim Southee to bowl from the other end.
On a length, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets forward and blocks it out.

Short of a length, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy hops and blocks it out.
On a good length, coming back in, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy nudges it to mid-wicket.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it sail through.
We are back for the middle session! The players stride out to the middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Shadman Islam to resume their innings. Trent Boult to start with the ball.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

A team performance by the visitors! Bangladesh needed five wickets and it did not take much time for them to bowl out New Zealand at 328 runs. All thanks to Mehidy Hasan. He was the star with the ball, as he picked up three wickets. This wouldn't have been possible without the early strike by Shoriful Islam. The onus is now on their batters to see of the next session without losing any wickets. But the Kiwis have a really solid arsenal when it comes to the bowling department. An enthralling session of cricket awaits. Do join us at 6.10 am IST (12.40 am GMT) for the second session.

The Kiwi batters fought till the very end. It was Conway and Young who built a solid foundation. Young slipped out after his half-ton while Conway snatched his first ton at home. Later, Nicholls played a crucial knock to make sure to cross the 300-run mark. New Zealand lost 5 wickets for just 70 runs. This tells you the story of their innings.

The first session clearly belonged to the visitors. First, they bowled out New Zealand before Lunch and later they managed to remain unscathed till the break. New Zealand could not add on their tally with the blade.
Length ball, outside off. Shadman Islam watches the ball closely and lets it sail through. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Length ball, in the fourth stump channel. Shadman Islam with a solid defence.
Good-length ball, outside off. Shadman Islam with an easy leave.
Nicely played! Fuller in length, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans onto it and drives it through covers. Neil Wagner gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Fullish, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to defend. The ball goes off the inside edge and rolls back past the stumps.

Edged but just short! Lovely piece of bowling from Boult! Good-length ball, on off, shaping away. Shadman Islam tries to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge but falls just short of Tim Southee at third slip.
Good-length ball, on top of off. Shadman Islam stands up on his toes and taps it to point.
Back of a length, outside off, nipping away. Shadman Islam watches the ball go past him.
Good bowling! Good-length ball, shaping away from off. Shadman Islam looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Bouncer from Boult, on middle. Shadman Islam sits under it.
Boult starts with a back-of-a-length ball, on off. Shadman Islam defends it towards covers.
Good-length ball, on off, swinging away. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it out off the front foot.
Trent Boult to bowl from the other end.
WIDE! Bangs a short ball, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks underneath. Wide called for height.
Length ball, around off, nipping away. Mahmudul Hasan Joy with a solid block.
Full again, outside off, shaping away. Mahmudul Hasan Joy reaches out for it and blocks it out.
Fuller and straighter, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on middle, coming back in this time. Shadman Islam flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single. Bangladesh are underway!
Tim Southee starts with a length ball, outside off, nipping away. Shadman Islam shoulders arms to it.

We are back for the final innings of the Test! The players of New Zealand stride out to the middle. Shadman Islam and Najmul Hossain Shanto walk out to bat for Bangladesh. Trent Boult will start with the ball.
...Fourth innings...

Right then! Bangladesh need just 40 runs to win and they are on the verge of creating history! Will the New Zealand bowlers get some early breakthroughs and make the chase interesting? We'll find that soon.

What a morning this is turning out to be for Bangladesh! They looked switched on right from the word go and have been absolutely brilliant against the World Test Champions. It was once again Ebadot Hossain who led from the front on Day 5 and got the big wicket of Ross Taylor. That set the tone for Bangladesh and they have conceded just 22 runs for taking the remaining 5 wickets on the final day of this Test. Taskin Ahmed and Ebadot Hossain have led the way for the tourists on Day 5 and they have been sensational. The overnight batters of New Zealand, Ross Taylor and Rachin Ravindra got out early and it was only Trent Boult who hit a couple of boundaries and extended the lead. New Zealand would have certainly hoped for more runs and they would be disappointed.

OUT! TAKEN! Another terrific catch and Bangladesh have been top-notch in the field on Day 5! A loopy delivery, around off. Trent Boult advances down the track and goes for a big one. He plays across the line again and heaves it with the lower part of his bat. The ball flies towards deep mid-wicket. Taijul Islam (sub) there, runs to his left and times his leap perfectly to take a sensational catch to dismiss Trent Boult. New Zealand are bundled out for 169! BANGLADESH NEED 40 RUNS TO WIN!
Commentary.Howout: c sub Taijul Islam b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller in length, outside off. Trent Boult defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, outside off. Trent Boult reaches out and blocks it towards point.
Flatter ball, around off. Trent Boult skips down and blocks it out.
Mehidy Hasan (22-5-43-0) comes into the attack.
Angling in around off, on a length. Neil Wagner plays across the line and goes for the pull shot but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On a length, around the fifth stump. Neil Wagner punches it to cover off the back foot.
Good-length delivery, around off. Neil Wagner looks to heave this but gets a thick inside edge on to his pads.
Length ball, outside off. Neil Wagner pushes it to cover.
Another length delivery, around the middle stump. Neil Wagner pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, on off. Neil Wagner blocks it off the back foot.
Shoriful Islam (11-1-30-0) comes to bowl now.
A length ball, down the leg side. Trent Boult goes for the flick but misses. Bangladesh think that he has got some bat on it and they appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved.
Fuller and wider of the off pole this time. Trent Boult swings hard at this but gets no bat on it.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Trent Boult blocks it out.
Taskin Ahmed drops it short this time, around leg. Trent Boult ducks underneath.
FOUR! Another boundary! Taskin Ahmed serves a length ball, wide of off. Trent Boult hangs back, and chops that aerially towards deep point for four.
FOUR! Nicley done! A full delivery, around off. Trent Boult drives it uppishly past mid off. The ball races away to the fence for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Left alone.
And again! Another length ball, outside off. Neil Wagner tries to block that but the ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, outside off. Neil Wagner goes for the drive but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Low full toss this time. Neil Wagner pushes it towards mid on.
Another full delivery, outside off. Neil Wagner drives it to cover fielder.
Fuller, on the stumps. Neil Wagner pushes it back to the bowler.
NOT OUT! Another shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! Good-length ball, outside off and nipping back in. Trent Boult looks to block but gets an inside edge onto the pad.

NOT OUT! Another shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! A full, inswinging ball. Trent Boult shuffles across and gets a slight edge onto his pads while going for his flick. Bangladesh appeal for LBW, but the umpire is unmoved.
Another full toss, on the body. Trent Boult defends it out.
Trent Boult is the last man in.

OUT BOWLED! Another one bites the dust! Taskin Ahmed strikes again and sends back Tim Southee. An inswinging low full toss by Taskin Ahmed which comes back in sharply from outside off. Tim Southee goes for the drive but the ball sneaks through and cannons onto his stumps. New Zealand are now 9 down.

Commentary.Commentary: Nipping back in again, on middle. Tim Southee blocks it out.

NOT OUT! A huge appeal for LBW but turned down! That did look close! A full delivery, shaping back in onto the pads. Tim Southee misses his flick and gets rapped on the pads. Bangladesh appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. That was probably sliding down leg.
A length ball, outside off. Neil Wagner, on the back foot, pushes it to cover.
On a length, shaping back in on middle. Neil Wagner defends that one.
Fuller this time, on middle. Neil Wagner dabs it towards cover.
Swing and a miss! Good-length ball, outside off. Neil Wagner swings hard at that one but fails to get any bat on it.
Back of a length, around middle, nipping back in. Neil Wagner blocks it out.
LEG BYE! A length ball, on the thigh pad. Tim Southee misses his flick and the ball deflects off his thigh pad and rolls towards fine leg. The batters steal a leg bye.

Taskin hurls a full ball, outside off and inviting the batter to drive. Rachin Ravindra looks for a booming drive through the cover region but he only manages an outside edge and Liton Das behind the sticks does the rest. Taskin Ahmed is pumped and Bangladesh seem to be in a hurry to finish things off on Day 5!

On a length, way outside off. Rachin Ravindra does not offer any shot to this one.
A bit fuller in length, outside off. Rachin Ravindra pushes it towards mid off.
Length ball, jagging back in from off. Rachin Ravindra defends it off the front foot.
Full ball, around off. Rachin Ravindra blocks it out.
Tim Southee comes to the crease now.

Length ball, angling down leg and going on with the angle. Kyle Jamieson misses his flick.
Length ball, angling down leg. Rachin Ravindra clips it towards fine leg and collects a run.

Short of a length, around middle. Rachin Ravindra keeps it out watchfully.
Length ball, around middle. Rachin Ravindra pushes it towards mid on.

Back of a length, around off. Kyle Jamieson prods and blocks it back to the bowler.

Just the kind of start that the tourists were hoping for and New Zealand are in deep trouble now and Taylor makes his way back to the pavilion.

Good-length ball, around off. Rachin Ravindra defends it out.

We are set for Day 5 to get underway! The players are out in the middle. Ross Taylor and Rachin Ravindra will resume their batting. Taskin Ahmed will begin the proceedings. Here we go...

New Zealand are World Test Champions but they were blown away a bit by the tourists on Day 4 and find themselves in some serious trouble coming into Day 5. They managed to bundle out Bangladesh just before Lunch on Day 4 and also started reasonably well with the bat. Will Young and Ross Taylor stitched together a crucial partnership of 73 runs but then came Ebadot Hossain's magical spell which completely shifted the momentum in Bangladesh's favour. Ross Taylor is still at the crease and New Zealand's hopes now rest on the veteran's shoulders. Rachin Ravindra too, looked solid in the middle and the Kiwis would be hoping that these two overnight batters bail them out of trouble. We are in for an intriguing day of Test cricket with all three results still possible. Who will come out victorious?

Bangladesh bowlers were brilliant on Day 4 and they were rewarded late in the day where Ebadot Hossain picked wickets in a cluster and ensured that Bangladesh stay in the pole position. There was spin on offer for the tourists' spinners and they bowled well but luck didn't go their way and the dropped catch of Ross Taylor didn't help Bangladesh's cause either. It was Ebadot Hossain who turned the game on its head in the final session and New Zealand's batters looked clueless in the middle. They will now be looking to get the remaining wickets without conceding too many runs and ensure that they get enough time to chase down the total.

Hello and a very warm welcome to the coverage of Day 5 of the first Test between New Zealand and Bangladesh. Day 4 saw the tourists continue their dominance in this Test and they are now on the verge of going 1-0 up in this two-match Test series. However, New Zealand are World Test Champions for a reason and they will give it their all on the final day of this Test.

Right then! Bangladesh have outplayed New Zealand yet again on Day 4. This Test match keeps getting interesting with each passing day! We could be able to witness something extraordinary on Day 5. The action continues on Wednesday, 5th January, 2022 at 3.30 am IST (10.00 pm GMT, previous day). But as you all know, you can join us well in advance for the buildup. Till then, take care and goodbye!

Dropped catches, misfields, run out chances missed, but still, Bangladesh sit comfortably in the driver's seat. They have been scintillating with the ball, Ebadot Hossain in particular. He has kept things simple, attacked the sticks, been aggressive, and has been rewarded for doing so. He got the important breakthrough of Will Young, and followed it up with two quick wickets of Henry Nicholls and Tom Blundell. Bangladesh are just inches away from creating history. They will be hoping to wrap things up and emerge victorious on Day 5.

Coming into the final session, New Zealand would have never thought of being in such kind of trouble. They have managed to lose three wickets in quick succession and face a tough challenge ahead of them. Their veteran, Ross Tayor, is still out there in the middle. He has looked solid in the middle but he is also riding his luck as he was dropped by Shadman Islam off Mehidy Hasan. Probably, a bit too optimistic here, but the hosts will be hoping that Taylor sticks around till the end and they get a substantial second innings lead. Rachin Ravindra  has been around for a while and he would be eager to stitch a good partnership with Taylor on Day 5. The World Test Champions have 5 wickets in hand to put up a defendable total and save them from drowning in the first Test of the series.

It is Bangladesh all the way! There's no stopping them in this Test. They have been dominating throughout this Test and will be going into Day 5 in a commanding position. Ebadot Hossain, is the Man of the Moment, who has sent back four New Zealand batters and has put the hosts in deep trouble. The Kiwis have ended Day 4 with a lead of just 17 runs and have 5 wickets in hand to put up a defendable total and save this Test which looks like an uphill task for them going ahead.

OUT! LBW! Ebadot Hossain bags another wicket! He has sent Tom Blundell back early. A length ball, nipping back in onto the pads. Tom Blundell hangs back, and misses his flick to get hit on the pads. A huge shout for LBW, this time the umpire raises his finger. Tom Blundell opts for a review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge confirms that there is no bat involved in that. The Ball Tracker shows three reds, which means Tom Blundell needs to depart and Ebadot Hossain grabs his fourth wicket. New Zealand lose a review here and have lost their fifth wicket.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ebadot Hossain

We are back for the final session of Day 4! The players of Bangladesh stride out to the middle and they are followed by Ross Taylor and Will Young who walk out to bat for New Zealand. Mehidy Hasan to start with the ball.

New Zealand still trail by 62 runs, they have lost two wickets, but also have one of their most experienced batter Ross Taylor, along with Will Young at the crease. Will Young has been there for a while, he has looked solid, but has got lucky on different occasions. Ross Taylor too, has survived a few nervy moments but he will be looking to score big and put the pressure back on Bangladesh. The visitors have carried their momentum with the ball, Mehidy Hasan has caused a lot of problems with his spin, Ebadot Hossain too has been attacking the stumps and has looked aggressive. A few more wickets in the final session will make the Bangladesh camp really happy. Do join us for the final session of the day at 8:30 am IST (3:00 am GMT).

An exciting session of Test cricket! Bangladesh have done well to pick up two wickets and their bowlers have conceded 58 runs in this session. They have caused all kinds of trouble to the New Zealand batters. They are certainly on top here. The visitors have done exceptionally well to take the wickets of Tom Latham and Devon Conway, and haven't allowed the batters to score freely.

The action now moves to Christchurch for the second Test of the series which starts from 9th January, 2022. Day 1 of this Test will begin at 3.30 am IST (10 pm GMT, previous night). But as you all know, you can join us well in advance for the buildup. Until then, goodbye and take care!

Mominul Haque, the victorious skipper of Bangladesh, says that it was all about team work that helped them win this match, they put all their efforts into batting, bowling and fielding. Mentions that they won because of the bowlers as they were outstanding in the first as well as the second innings. On being asked about Ebadot Hossain, he says that he has been unbelievable for them and was just outstanding. Concludes by saying that it was important to win this game and they have to forget about this win and look forward to the Christchurch Test now.

Tom Latham, the skipper of New Zealand, says that Bangladesh outplayed them and credits them for the way they played. Adds that they were not able to put on a huge total on the board in the first innings and somewhere around 450 would have been a good score. Says that they are hurt but goes onto say that Bangladesh deserve to win this Test as they have played some outstanding cricket. Mentions that they will prepare well for the next Test in Christchurch and now they have got an idea about Bangladesh's bowlers and batters as well and hopes that they will put on a better show at Christchurch.

Ebadot Hossain is the Player of the Match for his exceptional bowling performance in the second innings. He says that he is very happy and they had set a goal before coming to New Zealand. Says that they have come to New Zealand for the last 11 years and not won a single game. Adds that they wanted to beat the World Test Champions and set an example for the youngsters of their country. Tells that he has been working really hard with their head coach and it is paying off. Signs off by saying that his journey from volleyball to cricket is a long story and he is enjoying his cricket.
Stay tuned for the presentation!

The Word Test Champions have been defeated in their own backyard. Well, who saw that coming? New Zealand have been completely outplayed by Bangladesh. They started off well by putting a healthy total of 328 on the board, courtesy of a phenomenal century by Devon Conway. Henry Nicholls and Will Young made vital contributions as well. But their bowlers were not at their best, they failed to pick up wickets at regular intervals and also leaked quite a few runs. They had to toil hard to get Bangladesh all out. Coming into bat again, they could not repeat their performance. They kept losing wickets and were bundled out for 169, with a lead of just 39 runs in the second innings. New Zealand might have lost this game, but have another game to make amends and level the series.

A complete team performance here for the visitors. Four of their batters managed to go past the 50-run mark and that helped Bangladesh with a substantial lead in the first innings. Not to forget the contribution made by Mehidy Hasan as well. Talking about their bowling, Shoriful Islam and Mehidy Hasan grabbed 3 wickets each in the first innings. Skipper, Mominul Haque, also chipped in with 2 wickets at the end and dismissed the hosts for 328. Coming into the third innings of the game, it was all about Ebadot Hossain, who demolished the New Zealand batting order with his 6-fer. Taskin Ahmed was exceptional as well, as he scalped 3 wickets and helped his side bowl out the hosts. It was all too easy for them, they needed just 40 runs for victory, and they have chased it down by losing only a couple of wickets. They deserve every bit of this victory as they have been quite unreal in this game!

BANGLADESH WIN THE TEST MATCH AND LEAD THE SERIES 1-0. HISTORY HAS BEEN MADE! Bangladesh have pulled off something incredible here against the World Test Champions. They win their first ever Test match against New Zealand. This has been a sensational performance from the visitors. They have completely outplayed New Zealand and have certainly been the better team. A tough loss to digest for New Zealand as their 17-match unbeaten streak in Tests at home has finally been broken.
